<subSubSection box="[199,854,1545,1571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1545,1680]" box="[199,854,1545,1571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1545,1571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[709,757,1545,1571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1104,1581,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1545,1680]" box="[199,1104,1581,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1581,1607]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from Dabashan Mountains, 
<collectingRegion box="[818,1017,1581,1607]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Shaanxi Province</collectingRegion>
, 
